								interactions.
							</p>
						</div>
					</li>

					<li class="feature">
						<svg fill="#e44e25" width="64px" height="64px" viewBox="0 0 32 32">
							<path
								d="M30.039 2.719c-0.143-0.544-0.631-0.939-1.211-0.939-0.395 0-0.748 0.184-0.977 0.47l-0.002 0.002c-1.639 1.931-3.786 3.384-6.235 4.158l-0.096 0.026c-1.66 0.54-3.592 0.925-5.588 1.079l-0.086 0.005c-2.296 0.094-4.448 0.609-6.414 1.468l0.114-0.045c-3.466 1.876-5.78 5.485-5.78 9.633 0 0.064 0.001 0.127 0.002 0.19l-0-0.010c0.010 0.318 0.031 0.631 0.068 0.945 0.144 1.149 0.443 2.193 0.877 3.163l-0.028-0.070c-1.472 1.947-2.758 4.166-3.758 6.536l-0.076 0.204c-0.064 0.145-0.101 0.314-0.101 0.492 0 0.512 0.309 0.953 0.75 1.146l0.008 0.003c0.144 0.064 0.311 0.102 0.487 0.102 0.001 0 0.003 0 0.004 0h-0c0 0 0.001 0 0.001 0 0.512 0 0.953-0.308 1.146-0.75l0.003-0.008c0.863-2.053 1.833-3.813 2.96-5.455l-0.066 0.102c1.149 1.549 2.642 2.78 4.37 3.593l0.070 0.030c1.482 0.678 3.216 1.072 5.041 1.072 0.026 0 0.052-0 0.077-0l-0.004 0c1.957-0.008 3.82-0.406 5.517-1.119l-0.095 0.035c5.424-2.452 9.281-7.517 9.983-13.546l0.008-0.079c0.151-1.153 0.237-2.486 0.237-3.839 0-3.061-0.441-6.020-1.264-8.815l0.056 0.22zM28.537 14.781c-0.578 5.22-3.848 9.56-8.373 11.642l-0.090 0.037c-1.28 0.561-2.772 0.888-4.34 0.888-1.522 0-2.972-0.308-4.292-0.864l0.073 0.027c-1.604-0.758-2.91-1.921-3.822-3.358l-0.022-0.037c3.354-3.495 8.014-5.715 13.193-5.872l0.029-0.001c0.636-0.064 1.129-0.596 1.129-1.244 0-0.69-0.56-1.25-1.25-1.25-0.043 0-0.085 0.002-0.126 0.006l0.005-0c-5.472 0.226-10.391 2.428-14.097 5.906l0.012-0.011c-0.102-0.347-0.188-0.766-0.242-1.196l-0.004-0.042c-0.027-0.24-0.045-0.482-0.051-0.723-0.001-0.048-0.002-0.105-0.002-0.162 0-3.16 1.757-5.909 4.348-7.325l0.044-0.022c1.6-0.679 3.456-1.104 5.402-1.174l0.027-0.001c2.288-0.177 4.409-0.604 6.429-1.258l-0.195 0.055c2.238-0.74 4.171-1.848 5.83-3.267l-0.023 0.020c0.404 1.735 0.635 3.727 0.635 5.773 0 1.216-0.082 2.414-0.24 3.587l0.015-0.137z"
							></path>
						</svg>
						<div>
							<h3 class="feature__title">Faster and greener</h3>
							<p class="feature__description">
								Building with pure CSS means lighter pages, faster load times, and a smaller carbon footprint.
							</p>
						</div>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="testimonials">
			<h2 class="testimonials__title">Loved by the community</h2>

			<div class="testimonials__container">
				<ul class="testimonial__list">
					<li class="testimonial">
						<div class="testimonial__content">
							<Picture
								src={testimonial1}
								formats={['avif', 'webp', 'jpg']}
								width="168"
								height="168"
								alt="Second testimonial"
								class="testimonial__image"
							/>
							<p class="testimonial__author">Zark Muckerberg <br /> <span>Confused Developer</span></p>
						</div>
						<blockquote class="testimonial__text">
							Who needs fast pages anyway? I love waiting 5 seconds for a button to work. This book is a disaster.
						</blockquote>
					</li>

					<li class="testimonial">
						<div class="testimonial__content">
							<Picture
								src={testimonial2}
								formats={['avif', 'webp', 'jpg']}
								width="168"
								height="168"
								alt="Second testimonial"
								class="testimonial__image"
							/>
							<p class="testimonial__author">Melon Tusk <br /> <span>Former Framework Addict</span></p>
						</div>
						<blockquote class="testimonial__text">
							This book made me uninstall half my JavaScript libraries. My therapist will hear about this.
						</blockquote>
					</li>

					<li class="testimonial">
						<div class="testimonial__content">
							<Picture
								src={testimonial3}
								formats={['avif', 'webp', 'jpg']}
								width="168"
								height="168"
								alt="Second testimonial"
								class="testimonial__image"
							/>
							<p class="testimonial__author">Kim Coot <br /> <span>Hardcore JavaScript Fan</span></p>
						</div>
						<blockquote class="testimonial__text">HAHAHAHAHAHAHAHAHAHAHAHAHAHAH IMAGINE READING THIS.</blockquote>
					</li>

					<li class="testimonial">
						<div class="testimonial__content">
							<Picture
								src={testimonial4}
								formats={['avif', 'webp', 'jpg']}
								width="168"
								height="168"
								alt="Second testimonial"
								class="testimonial__image"
							/>
							<p class="testimonial__author">Parry Lage <br /> <span>Proud jQuery Defender</span></p>
						</div>
						<blockquote class="testimonial__text">
							Tried the CSS-only dropdown technique. It worked instantly. Honestly, it felt wrong.
						</blockquote>
					</li>

					<li class="testimonial">
						<div class="testimonial__content">
							<Picture
								src={testimonial5}
								formats={['avif', 'webp', 'jpg']}
								width="168"
								height="168"
								alt="Second testimonial"
								class="testimonial__image"
							/>
							<p class="testimonial__author">Beff Jezos <br /> <span>JavaScript Maximalist</span></p>
						</div>
						<blockquote class="testimonial__text">
							Was hoping for 300 pages of pure JS hacks. Got clean, maintainable CSS instead. 0/10.
						</blockquote>
					</li>

					<li class="testimonial">
						<div class="testimonial__content">
							<Picture
								src={testimonial1}
								formats={['avif', 'webp', 'jpg']}
								width="168"
								height="168"
								alt="Second testimonial"
								class="testimonial__image"
							/>
							<p class="testimonial__author">Pundar Sichai <br /> <span>Reluctant CSS Believer</span></p>
						</div>
						<blockquote class="testimonial__text">
							I opened this book expecting JavaScript magic. Instead, I got CSS reality. Absolute betrayal.
						</blockquote>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="faq">
			<h2 class="faq__title">Frequently asked questions</h2>

			<ul class="faq__container">
				<li class="accordion">
					<details open>
						<summary aria-describedby="accordion">
							<span role="term">Who is this ebook for? </span>
						</summary>
					</details>

					<div class="content">
						<p class="inner" role="definition" id="accordion">
							If you're a web developer who wants to build interactive components without relying on JavaScript — and
							you care about performance, clean code, and saving time — this book is for you.
						</p>
					</div>
				</li>

				<li class="accordion">
					<details>
						<summary aria-describedby="accordion">
							<span role="term">Do I need to be a CSS expert to follow along? </span>
						</summary>
					</details>

					<div class="content">
						<p class="inner" role="definition" id="accordion">
							You don't need to be an expert, but a basic understanding of CSS is recommended. The ebook is
							beginner-friendly, yet packed with tips and techniques that even seasoned developers will find valuable.
							You'll learn step-by-step through clear, practical examples.
						</p>
					</div>
				</li>

				<li class="accordion">
					<details>
						<summary aria-describedby="accordion">
							<span role="term">What exactly will I learn?</span>
						</summary>
					</details>

					<div class="content">
						<p class="inner" role="definition" id="accordion">
							You'll learn how to create real-world UI components (like tabs, modals, dropdowns) using only CSS. Plus,
							you'll discover methods to speed up your pages, write maintainable code, and reduce bugs.
						</p>
					</div>
				</li>

				<li class="accordion">
					<details>
						<summary aria-describedby="accordion">
							<span role="term">When will the ebook be available? </span>
						</summary>
					</details>

					<div class="content">
						<p class="inner" role="definition" id="accordion">
							The ebook is currently in preparation. Sign up with your email and you'll be the first to know as soon as
							it launches — and get an exclusive discount!
						</p>
					</div>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section class="cta">
			<h2 class="cta__title">Ready to build faster, cleaner, and greener?</h2>
